  "title": "Senior Quantity Surveyor / Contracts Manager",
  "description": "<ul><li>To manage and handle day-to-day operation of the Contracts / Tender, Pre & Post department.</li><li>Manpower planning and allocation/assignment of staff to various projects.</li><li>Lead a team of QS and guide them towards achieving the expected project delivery in accordance with the respective project’s requirements.</li><li>Familiar with PSSCOC, REDAS, SIA contractual legislations, and SOP Act</li><li>Lead in notification on the extension of time, contractual claims, variations, and any related loss and expense claims to the client and/or assessing and reviewing of extension of time, variations, and any related loss and expense claims by sub-contractors</li><li>Able to deal with disputes arises from project execution amicably with the relevant internal and external stakeholders</li><li>Provide procurement strategies and advise the key points of cost control in sub-contracting and potential variation orders to ensure provisions are catered for within cost and time.</li><li>Advice on negotiating contract terms and conditions with subcontractors/suppliers</li><li>Review, draft and prepare Sub-consultancy Agreement for the employment of Sub-Consultant by the company.</li><li>A good team player whom is able to perform contracts management duties and support the project managers in areas including contracts management, preparation and evaluation of tenders.</li><li>Estimate and formulate Construction cost – able to perform measurement to derive the quantity of works and provide budgetary/detailed construction cost.</li></ul><p><br /></p><p>Requirements:</p><p>Minimum 6 years of relevant experience in Senior QS function / mangerial role</p><p>Degree in Quantity Surveying / Contracts or Building</p><p><br /></p><p>@ mingyan@staffhub.com</p>",
